# Phase 2.5.2 — SPA fallback for Hostinger production.
#
# The Vite production build emits this file into dist/. Operators
# deploy dist/ to /public_html/app/ on Hostinger. Because the SPA
# is URL-aware (history.pushState on click navigation, popstate
# listener for back/forward, and parsePageFromUrl on mount), Apache
# must serve index.html for any unknown path so the front-end
# router can take over.
#
# Without this rule, hard-refreshing /app/checkout, /app/order/12,
# etc. would return a 404 and the routing fix has no effect.
#
# The "!-f" / "!-d" conditions ensure real files (CSS, JS, images,
# the index.html itself) and existing directories are served
# directly — only unmatched paths get rewritten.

Options -MultiViews
RewriteEngine On

RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d
RewriteRule ^ index.html [QSA,L]
